# health-front rules

- App Router: prefer server components by default; use `"use client"` only when needed.
- Don’t fetch `/api/me` from server components via relative `fetch()` unless you know cookies are included. Prefer `lib/backend.ts` helpers.
- Component imports should use the structured paths:
  - UI: `@/components/ui/*`
  - Layout: `@/components/layout/*`
  - Nav: `@/components/nav/*`
  - Auth: `@/components/auth/*`
  - Forms: `@/components/forms/*`
- PWA: dev/build must use webpack (`next dev --webpack`, `next build --webpack`).
- If you delete/move components and dev shows missing-file errors, clear `health-front/.next/`.

## Layout + navigation UI conventions

- Header layout: keep primary nav/title **left-aligned** and user menu/fullscreen **right-aligned** using `justify-between`.
- Header container: avoid hard `max-w-*` wrappers when you want true left/right alignment; use responsive padding (`px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`) instead.
- Sidebar:
  - Desktop: `md:block` with responsive widths (`md:w-*` / `lg:w-*`) and `h-full`.
  - Collapsed mode: hide section labels (e.g. don’t show “Nav/Navigation” when collapsed).
  - Mobile: render sidebar in the `md:hidden` overlay/drawer and ensure overlay z-index sits above sticky header/footer (`z-60`).

